  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "In the new fork choice rule section, a utility function `get_ancestor()` is defined as follows\r\n\r\n```\r\ndef get_ancestor(store, block, slot): return block if block.slot == slot else get_ancestor(store, store.get_parent(block), slot)\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf `block` has no ancestor at slot `slot` then this will fail to terminate. I think it is safe just to change `==` to `<=` here in the context of the whole algorithm, but it might be better to return some kind of null value in this case.",
